The paper focuses on content-based image retrieval using visual features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep representations also suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the optimization of factors affecting deep feature performance implies a focus on algorithmic improvements, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
